Sentencas: Coal syngases of various CO/H(2) ratios were used as the fuel over anode of solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Coal syngas reactivity over Ni-added LSCF-GDC anode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Anode materials of La(0.58)Sr(0.4)Co(0.2)Fe(0.8)O(3-delta) (LSCF)-gadolinia-doped ceria (CDC) composites and Ni-added LSCF-GDC were tested.
Titulo: Coal syngas reactivity over Ni-added LSCF-GDC anode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of CO is higher than that of H(2) and increases as the CO concentration in the CO + H(2) mixture increases.
Titulo: Coal syngas reactivity over Ni-added LSCF-GDC anode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As the LSCF content in the LSCF-GDC composites increases, the H(2) reactivity increases but the CO reactivity decreases.
Titulo: Coal syngas reactivity over Ni-added LSCF-GDC anode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of Ni-added LSCF-GDC is highest but the steady-state current density of LSCF-CDC can be higher than that of Ni-added LSCF-GDC via an induction period of activation.
Titulo: Coal syngas reactivity over Ni-added LSCF-GDC anode of solid oxide fuel cells
